window.__BLOG_POSTS__ = {
  "5km-personal-best.md": "---\ntitle: '5k PB! How good'\ndate: '19-04-2026'\nauthor: 'Lennon Winton'\ntags: ['sport', 'run']\nexcerpt: 'I achieved a new 5k PB!'\n---\n\nOn the 15<sup>th</sup> of April I acheived a new 5k PB!\n\nI got a time of **19:29**\n\nIt was only possible because I am an absolute weapon with a pair of running shoes.\n",
  "hello-blog.md": "---\ntitle: \"Hello Blog\"\ndate: \"05-03-2026\"\nauthor: \"Lennon Winton\"\ntags: [\"welcome\", \"introduction\"]\nexcerpt: \"This is my first blog post on my new site!\"\n---\n\n# Welcome to My Blog\n\nThis is my first blog post using my new site! I'm excited to start sharing my thoughts and all that jazz!\n\n## Why I Started This Blog\n\nThe idea of content creation is something that has always intrigued me and having my own space where I can share what I've been getting up to, seems cool to me. Especially, if I've built it myself.\nAnother reason for this is I want to improve my frontend dev skills as it is something I am doing more frequently at work, and I think this will be a fun way to learn and improve.\n\nStay tuned for more content!\n",
  "june-2026.md": "---\ntitle: 'The 2026 Birken Fjell Marathon'\ndate: '30-06-2026'\nauthor: 'Lennon Winton'\ntags: ['sport', 'run']\nexcerpt: 'Birken Fjell Marathon'\n---\n\nThe Birken Fjell Marathon went down on the 13<sup>th</sup> of June. It was wet, muddy, and tough, but such a fun time. I wouldn't have wanted it any other way.\n",
  "may-2026.md": "---\ntitle: 'Whatta month!'\ndate: '31-05-2026'\nauthor: 'Lennon Winton'\ntags: ['sport', 'run', 'climb', 'music']\nexcerpt: 'big months with big things'\n---\n\nThis has been a big month with big things.\n\nComing into this month I didn't imagine it being as eventful as it was. With the Birken trail marathon happening in June, I thought I'd just be training for it and keeping it low-key till the race.\n\nHowever, I've had some pretty standout moments. The ones that come to mind first are the Joey Valence and Brae, and Tame Impala concerts, both being some of the best concerts I've seen. It was back to back days of sick music! JVB was pure energy and moshing, while Tame Impala was on it with the light show and atmosphere.\n\nOn top of that I've just been on one when it comes to the sports I've been doing. Following from last month's 5K race, I've had another PB. This time I've cut it down to 19:08! How good! Now I'm so keen to get the sub-19. I thought I'd be taking it chill with running post marathon, but it's goals like this that keep me coming back.\n\nIn terms of climbing I haven't been pushing my highest grade, but I've been getting more consistent and problems that I've been trying once every few months on the Moonboard are going down with not crazy amounts of effort. On the 2016 Moonboard I've been slowly ticking off a couple of V4 benchmarks each session. On the 2017 Moonboard there's a V7 benchmark I've been trying and I keep on falling off going for the last hold. It feels so doable and I reckon next time I give it a proper go, it'll go down. If I get it, it'll be the hardest climb I've done grade-wise... However, I think it is soft for the grade.\n\nTo quickfire some other things that have happened this month:\n\n- Plenty of birthday celebrations\n- Friends visiting us\n- A Sketchy Beats night\n- A trip to London\n\nWhatta month!\n"
};
